{  
 .......  
 var resultset = await rep.B(input1,input2);  
 return resultset;   
}

and B() alsi is marked with async/await .. so in this case method A() will execute till it finds await synchronously and when it finds await .. it will wait for B() to complete . Right ? So "rerurns from the async method " you said ? It returns to what ? And if there is nothing to execute after returning . in that context "It is something synchronous execution only .. right ? Means

instead of var resultset = await rep.B(input1,input2);

I could have written var resultset = rep.B(input1,input2); only . It also does not proceed untill B() is finished ? What am I missing ?
